There were two issues brought to my attention recently:

<https://jira.hyperledger.org/browse/FAB-347>
<https://jira.hyperledger.org/browse/FAB-191>

Jim has verified that FAB-191 no longer occurs. Someone commented on FAB-347 just recently and said that yes, it still occurs. I have not tried it myself. Gabor are you planning to verify this one? It looks like it’s already assigned to you, not sure how that happened?
<https://jira.hyperledger.org/browse/FAB-347I> checked master with master and 0.6 with 0.6 and it worked
last message by Ryo: " However, the returned value is different from the expected value. It returns the following message:"
it seems he got 100 as a hex
right, that is what he is saying… i have honestly never observed that. but he is attaching a specific app to that bug. i did not test with that specific app.
someone else also had this problem, he got a hexadecimal number when querying
but I think this is unrelated to the original problem described in FAB-347
